Space Lounge and Grill on Ngong' Road in Nairobi has been ordered to close operations for the second time over noise pollution.The order came on Thursday after it failed to comply with agreements it signed with area residents and the county.A letter from the county noted the club's management has not complied with directives on noise levels. Residents are still annoyed and disturbed by the noise emitted by your business," the management was told.The county added that the establishment has continued running the business despite the expiry of liquor licences on October 8. You are still in operation when your single business permit was revoked on September 22," the letter also read. The club was temporarily closed in August following a successful petition by residents who cited excessive noise pollution.Read: Court orders Space Lounge closed for noise pollution